{
  "texts": [
    "This paradigm has been shown to achieve a degree of agreement (over 80%) that is comparable to that of human experts, and thus it offers a mechanism to automate custom validation and verification tasks.",
    "Although LLM-as-a-judge is imperfect, it is the only alternative to human assessment, which is more reliable but impractical in the context of evaluating LLM-generated content.",
    "• We characterize further potential contributions and longterm vision of MDE in the context of prompt engineering.Naturally, this DSL and toolkit are not intended for prompts that will be used just once and then thrown away, e.g., in a trial-and-error manner.",
    "Instead, the contributions of this paper are intended for recurring prompts, e.g., prompts that are valuable for a particular organization because they are used as part of a business or engineering process.This paper is the extended version of the paper \"Modeldriven prompt engineering\" published in the 26th ACM/IEEE International Conference on Model-Driven Engineering Languages and Systems (MODELS'2023).",
    "In this extended submission, we have added (a) an updated analysis of the state of the art, including the discussion of complex tasks (Sect. 2.4); (b) code generation capabilities to query generative AI systems with the generated prompts (Sect."
  ]
}